---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Bathroom Wall Tile Calculator — Estimate Tiles & Boxes | CalcForDIY"
  description="Calculate how much tile you need for bathroom walls. Enter wall dimensions, subtract door, window, and vanity areas, and get square footage and box count instantly. Free, no signup."
>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "Bathroom Wall Tile Calculator",
    "description": "Free bathroom wall tile calculator that estimates tile square footage and box count including waste factor.",
    "applicationCategory": "CalculatorApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Web Browser",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" }
  }
  </script>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a>
    <span>/</span>
    <span>Bathroom Wall Tile Calculator</span>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Bathroom Wall Tile Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">Enter your bathroom wall dimensions to get an accurate tile estimate — subtract doors, windows, and vanity areas for a precise box count.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">1</span>
      Wall Measurements
    </h2>

    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">Measure each wall from floor to where tiling ends (not necessarily ceiling height). Width is corner to corner.</p>

    <!-- Wall 1 -->
    <div class="mb-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-3">Wall 1 <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-normal">(required)</span></p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Height</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="w1h_ft" placeholder="8" min="0" max="20"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="w1h_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Width</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="w1w_ft" placeholder="6" min="0" max="100"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="w1w_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Wall 2 -->
    <div class="mb-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-3">Wall 2 <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-normal">(required)</span></p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Height</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="w2h_ft" placeholder="8" min="0" max="20"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="w2h_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Width</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="w2w_ft" placeholder="5" min="0" max="100"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="w2w_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Wall 3 optional -->
    <div class="mb-3">
      <label class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-3 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50">
        <input type="checkbox" id="wall3Toggle" class="w-4 h-4 rounded text-blue-600" onchange="toggleSection('wall3Section', this.checked)" />
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">+ Add Wall 3</span>
      </label>
      <div id="wall3Section" class="hidden mt-3 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-3">Wall 3</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Height</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="w3h_ft" placeholder="8" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="w3h_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Width</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="w3w_ft" placeholder="6" min="0" max="100"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="w3w_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Wall 4 optional -->
    <div class="mb-5">
      <label class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-3 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50">
        <input type="checkbox" id="wall4Toggle" class="w-4 h-4 rounded text-blue-600" onchange="toggleSection('wall4Section', this.checked)" />
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">+ Add Wall 4</span>
      </label>
      <div id="wall4Section" class="hidden mt-3 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-3">Wall 4</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Height</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="w4h_ft" placeholder="8" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="w4h_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Width</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="w4w_ft" placeholder="5" min="0" max="100"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="w4w_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-5 border-gray-200" />

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">2</span>
      Subtract Openings (Optional)
    </h2>

    <!-- Door -->
    <div class="mb-3">
      <label class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-3 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50">
        <input type="checkbox" id="doorToggle" class="w-4 h-4 rounded text-blue-600" onchange="toggleSection('doorSection', this.checked)" />
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Subtract door opening</span>
      </label>
      <div id="doorSection" class="hidden mt-3 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Door Height</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="dh_ft" placeholder="6" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="dh_in" placeholder="8" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Door Width</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="dw_ft" placeholder="2" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="dw_in" placeholder="6" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Window -->
    <div class="mb-3">
      <label class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-3 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50">
        <input type="checkbox" id="windowToggle" class="w-4 h-4 rounded text-blue-600" onchange="toggleSection('windowSection', this.checked)" />
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Subtract window</span>
      </label>
      <div id="windowSection" class="hidden mt-3 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Window Height</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="wh_ft" placeholder="2" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="wh_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Window Width</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="ww_ft" placeholder="3" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="ww_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Vanity / mirror area -->
    <div class="mb-5">
      <label class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer p-3 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50">
        <input type="checkbox" id="vanityToggle" class="w-4 h-4 rounded text-blue-600" onchange="toggleSection('vanitySection', this.checked)" />
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Subtract vanity / mirror area</span>
      </label>
      <div id="vanitySection" class="hidden mt-3 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-3">The wall area behind a vanity mirror or cabinet that will not be tiled.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Area Height</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="vh_ft" placeholder="3" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="vh_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Area Width</label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input type="number" id="vw_ft" placeholder="4" min="0" max="20"
                class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
              <input type="number" id="vw_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
                class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-5 border-gray-200" />

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">3</span>
      Tile Settings
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-5">
      <div>
        <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Installation Pattern</label>
        <select id="pattern"
          class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
          <option value="straight">Straight / Brick (10% waste)</option>
          <option value="diagonal">Diagonal / Offset (15% waste)</option>
          <option value="herringbone">Herringbone (20% waste)</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">
          Box Coverage <span class="text-gray-400 font-normal text-xs">(from your tile box)</span>
        </label>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <input type="number" id="boxCoverage" placeholder="e.g. 10.8" min="0.1" step="0.1"
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 shrink-0">sq ft / box</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Leave blank to skip box count</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <button onclick="calculate()"
      class="w-full bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors text-base">
      Calculate Tile Needed →
    </button>

  </div>

  <div id="errorMsg" class="hidden bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 text-red-700 text-sm">
    Please enter at least two wall measurements to calculate.
  </div>

  <div id="results" class="hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">Your Tile Estimate</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center shadow-sm">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900" id="r_area">—</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Net Wall Area</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center shadow-sm">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700" id="r_waste">—</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Waste Factor</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center shadow-sm">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900" id="r_total">—</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Total to Buy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center shadow-sm" id="r_boxRow">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700" id="r_boxes">—</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Boxes Needed</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-blue-800 mt-4 bg-blue-200 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-3">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> Always buy one extra box. Tile dye lots change between production runs — matching tiles later is difficult.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">How to Use This Calculator</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Using this bathroom wall tile calculator is simple. Follow these steps to get a highly accurate estimate of the materials you need:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">1</span>
        <span><strong>Measure each wall.</strong> Use a tape measure to find the exact height and width of your first two bathroom walls in feet and inches.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">2</span>
        <span><strong>Add more walls as needed.</strong> If you are tiling a larger space or a fully enclosed room, you can add measurements for up to four walls.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">3</span>
        <span><strong>Subtract door, window, and vanity areas.</strong> Enter the dimensions of any structural openings or large fixtures that will not receive tile. This ensures you do not over-order.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">4</span>
        <span><strong>Select your tile pattern.</strong> Choose how you plan to lay the tile, as complex patterns require more cuts and generate more waste.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">5</span>
        <span><strong>Enter box coverage.</strong> Check the label on your specific tile box to see how many square feet it covers, allowing the calculator to provide a precise box count.</span>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Formula</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">This bathroom wall tile calculator determines your material needs based on guidelines from the Tile Council of North America (TCNA). Here is how the math works:</p>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 mb-5 font-mono text-sm text-gray-800 space-y-1">
      <p>Total Wall Area = Sum of all individual wall areas</p>
      <p>Net Area = Total Wall Area − (Doors + Windows + Vanity)</p>
      <p>With Waste = Net Area × Waste Factor</p>
      <p>Boxes = Math.ceil(With Waste / Box Coverage)</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-700">First, the total area is calculated by adding the square footage of all your walls. Next, the square footage of any doors, windows, and vanity areas is subtracted to find your net area. A waste factor is then applied based on your pattern: 10% for straight or brick layouts, 15% for diagonal layouts, and 20% for intricate herringbone patterns. Finally, the total square footage including waste is divided by your box coverage, and always rounded up to the nearest whole box.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-5">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Should I tile behind the toilet?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes. It is considered standard practice to tile completely behind the toilet tank. Skipping this area can leave a visible gap, makes future toilet replacements difficult if the new tank is smaller, and removes the water-resistant barrier where leaks are common.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">How high should I tile my bathroom walls?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">There are two common approaches. Wainscoting height typically stops between 36 and 42 inches up the wall, often capped with a chair rail tile. Alternatively, you can tile the entire wall up to the ceiling (typically 84 to 96 inches) for a dramatic, fully waterproof space.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Should I include the area behind the vanity cabinet?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Usually, no. If you are installing a standard base cabinet vanity that sits flush against the wall, you can leave that wall area untiled to save money and materials. However, if you are installing a pedestal sink or a floating vanity, you must tile the entire wall behind it.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">What tile size works best for small bathrooms?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Surprisingly, large-format tiles (like 12x24 inches) can make a small bathroom feel larger because they create fewer visual grout lines, making the wall appear less cluttered. Medium sizes like 4x12 subway tiles are also highly popular and proportionate for smaller walls.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Do accent tiles need a separate calculation?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes. If you are adding a decorative stripe or mosaic band, use a bathroom wall tile calculator to figure out the square footage of the accent tile separately. Then, subtract that accent square footage from your main wall tile total.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Does subway tile count as a straight or offset pattern?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Traditional subway tile is laid in an offset (or running bond) pattern. While offset patterns usually require slightly more cuts than a grid, standard 50/50 subway tile cuts can often be reused on the opposite end of the wall. Because of this, it generally falls safely into the 10% straight/brick waste category.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Calculators</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
